ndicates value creation which apparently is the only reason shares rally the cost of equity can be estimated through a popular and nobelprize winning method called capital asset pricing model capm with a few sets of assumptions the capm pegs ovly’s cost of equity at  compared to its roe of  oak valley bancorp nasdaqcmovly last perf jul th  using dupont analysis we find out that roe is composed of three ratios profit margin asset turnover and financial leverage the method reflects the impact of change in key figures in both the income statement and the balance sheet the analysis provides a bird’seye view on the strengths and weaknesses of the company dupont formula roe  annual net profit ÷ shareholders’ equity roe  annual net profit ÷ sales × sales ÷ assets × assets ÷ shareholders’ equity roe  profit margin × asset turnover × financial leverage among the ratios affecting roe the profit margin is the most important as it highlights the operational efficiency of a company to a potential investor the ideal scenario would be profit increasing at a higher rate than the revenueoak valley bancorp’s roa over the past  months stood at  versus the industry’s  although an investor should look at multiyear asset turnover to assess its effect on the latest roe a quick comparison with the industry tells him whether it’s acceptable we use roa for the comparison as along with sales used in asset turnover earnings used in roa are also comparable within the industry oak valley bancorp nasdaqcmovly historical debt jul th  the last but not the least is the financial leverage it’s an important ratio as a company can hide its poor operating and assetuse efficiency by increasing leverage thus along with roe we should look at the return on capital which reflects earnings as a percentage of overall capital employed including debt for ovly roc stood at  versus the industry’s  roe – it’s not just another ratio roe is called the mother of all ratios for a reason it helps gauge a company’s efficiency both through the income statement and the balance sheet along with telling you how just changing the capital structure of the company can impact perceived return what are the analysts thinking about oak valley bancorp’s roe in three years i recommend you see our latest free analysis report to find out if you are not interested in ovly anymore you can use our free platform to see my list of stocks with return on equity over  top undervalued stocks for  looking for undervalued stocks the trick is not to follow the herd these overlooked companies are now trading for less than their intrinsic value click here to see them for free on the simply wall st platform share this article alex johannesen alex grew up a shrewd saver of his job and pocket money and eventually made his first investment at the age of  buying a few apple shares with his father’s brokerage account hooked ever since alex began advising friends and relatives on stock ideas and investment strategies going on to study management and financial studies in wales he now operates his own boutique wealth management advisory firm reach alex by sending an email at alexjohannesensimplywallstcom previous post what analysts think about exelon corporations exc growth next post what should investors know about the future of bhp billiton limiteds asxbhp business popular posts can snap inc snap turn things around audioboom group plc boom says it’s ideally placed to capitalise on the next internet revolution why domino’s pizza group plc dom shares nosedived despite strong profit growth microsoft corporation msft rides high on growing demand for cloud computing super retail group asxsul looks for competitive edge streamlines sports retail business ovly’s investment overview oak valley bancorpclick for free nasdaqcmovly research report ovly’s competitors nasdaqgsppbi pacific premier bancorp click for free research report nasdaqgswabc westamerica bancorporation click for free research report nasdaqgssasr sandy spring b